<p>Create a <a href="/glossary/topic-clustering/">content cluster</a> for each pest type. One pillar page per pest. 3 to 5 supporting blog posts per cluster. Internal links connecting them all.</p>
<h2>Google Business Profile Optimization for Pest Control</h2>
<p>Your <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a> is the single most important ranking factor for the local map pack. <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-google-business-profiles/">87% of consumers</a> use Google to find local businesses. A complete GBP profile is <a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-google-business-profiles/">7 times more likely</a> to get clicks than an incomplete one.</p>
<h3>Complete Every Field</h3>
<p>Google rewards complete profiles. Fill in every available field.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Business name (exact legal name, no keyword stuffing)</li>
<li>[ ] Primary category: Pest Control Service</li>
<li>[ ] Secondary categories: Termite Control Service, Exterminator, Wildlife Control Service</li>
<li>[ ] Service area (list every city and zip code you serve)</li>
<li>[ ] Business hours (including seasonal hours)</li>
<li>[ ] Phone number (local number, not toll-free)</li>
<li>[ ] Website URL</li>
<li>[ ] Business description (750 characters, include pest types and service areas)</li>
<li>[ ] Services list with descriptions and pricing ranges</li>
<li>[ ] Attributes: Women-owned, veteran-owned, emergency service available</li>
</ul>
<h3>Post Weekly to Your GBP</h3>
<p>Google tracks how often you post. Active profiles rank higher. Pest control has natural content opportunities every week.</p>
<p><strong>Weekly post ideas:</strong>
- Seasonal pest alerts ("Termite swarming season starts this month in [City]")
- Customer success stories (with permission)
- Before/after pest treatment photos
- Pest identification tips
- Special offers for seasonal treatments
- Community involvement and events</p>
<p><a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">GBP posts</a> appear directly in your listing. They give potential customers a reason to click your profile over a competitor with no recent activity.</p>
<h3>Photos and Videos</h3>
<p>Listings with photos get 42% more direction requests and 35% more website clicks. Upload 5 to 10 photos minimum.</p>
<p><strong>Photo types that work for pest control:</strong>
- Uniformed technicians at work
- Company vehicles (branded)
- Before/after treatment results
- Team photos
- Equipment and technology
- Office exterior</p>
<p>Update photos monthly. Fresh visual content signals an active, professional operation.</p>
