<h2>Service Area Pages: Rank in Every City You Serve</h2>
<p>Most pest control companies serve 10 to 30 cities within their region. Each city needs its own page. A single "service areas" page with a list of city names does not rank. Individual <a href="/blog/city-service-landing-pages-seo/">city-specific pages</a> do.</p>
<h3>What Each Service Area Page Needs</h3>
<p>Every city page should include:</p>
<p><strong>Unique content per city.</strong> Do not copy the same text and swap the city name. Google detects duplicate content. Write specific information about pest problems in that area. Mention local landmarks, neighborhoods, and pest patterns.</p>
<p><strong>Pest-specific service listings.</strong> List every pest type you treat in that city. Include brief descriptions and pricing ranges.</p>
<p><strong>Local contact information.</strong> If you have a local number for that area, use it. Include the address of your nearest office.</p>
<p><strong>Customer reviews from that city.</strong> Embed or quote reviews from customers in the specific service area.</p>
<p><strong>Schema markup.</strong> Add <a href="/glossary/schema-markup/">LocalBusiness schema</a> to every service area page. Include service area, geo coordinates, and service types.</p>
<h3>URL Structure for Service Area Pages</h3>
<p>Use a clean, keyword-rich URL structure.</p>
<pre><code>/pest-control-[city]/
/termite-treatment-[city]/
/bed-bug-exterminator-[city]/
</code></pre>
<p>Each URL targets the high-intent keyword for that city. A page at <code>/pest-control-austin/</code> targets "pest control Austin." A page at <code>/termite-treatment-dallas/</code> targets "termite treatment Dallas."</p>
<h3>How Many Pages to Create</h3>
<p>Start with your top 5 revenue cities. Create one main pest control page per city. Then expand to 10, 15, and eventually all service areas. Each page should have a minimum of 400 words of unique content.</p>
<p>This is <a href="/blog/programmatic-seo-guide/">programmatic SEO</a> applied to local services. The structure scales. The content must stay unique.</p>
