<h3>Publishing Cadence</h3>
<p>Publish pest content 30 to 60 days before peak search volume for that pest. Google needs time to crawl, index, and rank new content. A termite article published in January ranks by March when searches peak.</p>
<p>Consistency matters more than volume. Publishing <a href="/blog/how-many-blog-posts-to-rank/">20 to 30 articles per month</a> builds authority faster than publishing 5 articles in one month and nothing for the next 3.</p>
<h3>Content Types That Work for Pest Control</h3>
<p><strong>Identification guides.</strong> "What does a termite look like?" These are high-volume, low-competition keywords that attract homeowners at the start of a pest problem.</p>
<p><strong>Cost guides.</strong> "How much does pest control cost?" and "Termite treatment cost." These attract price-conscious buyers who are ready to hire.</p>
<p><strong>Comparison content.</strong> "DIY pest control vs professional exterminator." This positions your service as the better option with data and expertise.</p>
<p><strong>Prevention guides.</strong> "How to prevent ants in your kitchen." These build <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical authority</a> and keep your site top of mind.</p>
<p><strong>Emergency content.</strong> "What to do if you find a scorpion in your house." These capture urgent, high-intent searches.</p>
