<h2>Technical SEO for Pest Control Websites</h2>
<p>A pest control website does not need complex technical SEO. It needs the basics done correctly. Most pest control sites fail on mobile speed, missing schema, and poor URL structure.</p>
<h3>Mobile-First Design</h3>
<p>76% of <a href="/glossary/local-seo/">local searches</a> happen on mobile devices. For pest control, that number is likely higher. A homeowner finding a scorpion in their bathroom is not sitting at a desktop computer.</p>
<p>Your site must load in under 3 seconds on mobile. Check your <a href="/glossary/core-web-vitals/">Core Web Vitals</a> in Google Search Console. Fix any pages with poor LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) scores.</p>
<h3>Schema Markup</h3>
<p>Add structured data to every page. Pest control businesses should implement:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>LocalBusiness schema</strong> on the homepage and every service area page</li>
<li><strong>Service schema</strong> on each pest type service page</li>
<li><strong>FAQ schema</strong> on any page with frequently asked questions</li>
<li><strong>Review schema</strong> on pages featuring customer testimonials</li>
</ul>
<p>Schema helps Google understand your business, services, and locations. It also enables rich results in search listings.</p>
