<p>Avoid parameter-heavy URLs, session IDs, or unnecessary subdirectories. A flat URL structure helps both Google and users.</p>
<h3>Internal Linking Strategy</h3>
<p>Every page on your site should link to at least 2 to 3 other relevant pages. Create clear pathways between content.</p>
<ul>
<li>Homepage links to all service pages and top city pages</li>
<li>Service pages link to related blog posts and city pages</li>
<li>Blog posts link to relevant service pages and other blog posts</li>
<li>City pages link to the main service page and local blog content</li>
</ul>
<p>Strong <a href="/blog/internal-linking-blog-posts/">internal linking</a> distributes ranking authority across your site. It also helps visitors find related content and move toward booking a service.</p>
